It looks like this is documented incorrectly. The `botAvatarInitials` and the `userAvatarInitials` need to be set in the style options.

```javascript
const styleOptions = {
  botAvatarInitials: &#39;BF&#39;,
  userAvatarInitials: &#39;WC&#39;
};

window.WebChat.renderWebChat({
    directLine: window.WebChat.createDirectLine({secret: &#39;YOUR_BOT_SECRET&#39;}),
    styleOptions
  },
  document.getElementById(&#39;webchat&#39;)
);
```

For more details, take a look at the [Display User and Bot Initials](https://github.com/microsoft/BotFramework-WebChat/tree/master/samples/04.a.display-user-bot-initials-styling) Web Chat sample.

